data.title: coin, 1 cent, East Africa and Uganda Protectorates
data.meta_description: A Ugandan 1 cent coin, circular with machined aperture through centre, the obverse features crown and denomination "1 CENT" with flourishes and legends flanking the aperture reading "GEORGIVS V" "REX ET IND:IMP:", the reverse features tusks which flank the centre hole and denomination "1" encircled by legend "EAST AFRICA & UGANDA PROTECTORATES 1916".
data.text:
We have over a million object records online, and we are adding to this all the time. Our records are never finished. Sometimes we discover new information that changes what we know about an object, such as who made it or used it. Sometimes we change how an object is interpreted. We sometimes make mistakes in our spelling, transcription or categorisation, or miss information out of our records.
